The aim of the course is to give an overview of psychology as a research field and as a profession. The focus is on the central ideas, concepts and problems in psychology, that have been most publicly discussed and influential.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of psychology as a research field and as a profession.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course students: 1) use the main facts and concepts of psychology 2) can give good reasons for their opinions and presents them in written form 3) analyze what psychologists do and how contemporary psychology deals with its professional problems  4) distinguish between some legends/folk psychology and factual knowledge about human psyche 5) analyze how scientific psychological knowledge is formed.
